<p><b>Raymond McGovern</b> (born 1939) is a retired <a href="/wiki/CIA" title="CIA" class="mw-redirect">CIA</a> officer turned <a href="/wiki/Political_activism" title="Political activism" class="mw-redirect">political activist</a>. McGovern was a Federal employee under seven U.S. presidents over 27 years, presenting the morning intelligence briefings at the <a href="/wiki/White_House" title="White House">White House</a> for many of them.</p>
